text: Porta Westfalica is a city of the district of Minden-Lübbecke in the German state of North Rhine-Westphalia. It has about 37,000 inhabitants. The name "Porta Westfalica" is Latin and means "gate to Westphalia". == References == == Other websites == * Category:Minden-Lübbecke Rural District
title: Porta Westfalica
